Competition Doom is a Doom source port based on Chocolate Doom
and adds additional features and settings to it.



== Configuration File ==

Competition Doom also provides some extra settings.
These are stored in a file named 'cndoom.cfg'.

Detailed explanation about each setting:

// Competition Doom ID (required for demo submission)
// You have to register on forum http://www.doom.com.hr/forum/
// and request ID there or send request to cndoom@doom.com.hr
// Default: 0 (means your record will NOT BE VALID!)
cn_meta_id                    0

// Delay starting the game in milliseconds (0 - 9999) so you can
// adjust/press your mouse and key before the game starts
// 0 - 9999 (Default: 50)
cn_quickstart_delay           50

// Display in-game/intermission screen timer
// 0 - No, 1 - Yes (Default)
cn_timer_enabled              1

// Timer X position
// Default: -1
cn_timer_offset_x             -1

// Timer Y position
// Default: 0
cn_timer_offset_y             0

// Timer color
// 0 - 255 (Default: 168)
cn_timer_color_index          168

// Shadow for timer
// 0 - No (Default), 1 - Yes
cn_timer_shadow_index         0

// Background color for timer
// 0 - 255 (Default:16)
cn_timer_bg_colormap          16

// Pre-cache all sounds at start, otherwise game will 'skip/lag'
// when new sound is loaded.
// 0 - No, 1 - Yes (Default)
cn_precache_sounds            1

// Display "Secret is revealed!" only in demo playback.
// 0 - No (Default), 1 - Yes
cn_secret_message             0

// Define keyboard delay between keypreses.
// 0 - 1000 (Default: 200)
cn_typematic_delay            200

// Define keyboard character rate per second.
// 0 - 30 (Default: 30)
cn_typematic_rate             30


== Additional Competition Doom command-line options ==

-quickstart x   Delay starting the game in milliseconds (0 - 9999)
                so you can adjust/press your mouse and key

-printstats     Outputs gameplay stats per map/total to stdout/console

-speed          Use when recording speed category

-max            Use when recording max category

-nmare          Use when recording nightmare category

-nm100s         Use when recording Nightmare 100% secrets category

-tyson          Use when recording tyson category

-pacifist       Use when recording pacifist category

-episode x      Use when recording episode movie (Doom and Doom 2)
                Combine category and episode eg. cndoom -speed -episode 2

-movie          Use when recording movie (Doom and Doom 2)
                Combine category and movie eg. cndoom -max -movie



== Requirements ==

For Windows:
- DirectX 9.0c
- Microsoft .NET Framework 2.0 or higher (required only for launcher)

For Win 9x, use -gdi command line option or start setup and change
video_driver. All files, patches and fixes can be downloaded from here:
    http://doom.com.hr/cndoom/support/ 



== Troubleshooting ==
Q: Game runs slow/lags.
A: If on Windows, in setup select DirectX video driver and 16bit color.
   Select it under Setup -> Display -> Advanced

Q: Screen is blank/black for a long time.
A: In setup under Advanced settings set Quickstart and Startup delay to 0.

Report other issues/bugs/fixes here:
    https://github.com/fx02/cndoom/issues



